Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.25,0:18:40.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 謝了兄弟    - 夥計，這是個女人？\N{\rENG}- Thanks, bro.    - That's a girl, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.05,0:18:44.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,冒失鬼，我想你是對的 看看她的小奶子，就象蚊子咬的包\N{\rENG}Flip, I think you right. Look at her little bitty titties. They're like mosquito bites.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.59,0:18:47.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,靠，一嘴都含不滿 讓我看看\N{\rENG}Man, that's barely even a mouthful. Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:49.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看了你上一場比賽，謝瑞爾\N{\rENG}Saw your last fight, Shawrelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.22,0:18:52.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,大多數時間臉都朝下 我還意味地板長了奶子呢\N{\rENG}Spent so much time face down, I thought the canvas had titties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.83,0:19:02.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,地板長了奶子 嘿，看看我，我是謝瑞爾\N{\rENG}Canvas has titties. Hey, look at me. I'm Shawrelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.10,0:19:13.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟拳臺做啊 跟地板做啊\N{\rENG}Just humping the canvas. Humping the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.30,0:19:18.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,靠，兄弟，地板長了奶子？ 挺搞笑的，兄弟\N{\rENG}Come on, bro. The floor having titties? That's funny, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.54,0:19:22.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,閉嘴吧你 你們笑什麼呢\N{\rENG}Shut up, man. What you laughing at?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.24,0:19:24.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,哥們兒，扶住沙袋，傻瓜\N{\rENG}Man, hold the bag, stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:27.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,那邊有奶子啊，哥們兒\N{\rENG}Some titties right there, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.75,0:19:32.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,冒失鬼，他們什麼時候 開始做男式緊身褲了？\N{\rENG}Yo, when they start making those tights for men, Flippy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.21,0:19:34.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,廢物\N{\rENG}Punk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.99,0:19:38.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了，足夠了 今天足夠了\N{\rENG}All right, that's enough. That's enough for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.79,0:19:43.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我給你按摩一下    - 噢，我沒時間，弗蘭基\N{\rENG}- I'll give you a rubdown.    - Oh, I can't, Frankie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.52,0:19:46.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子有鋼琴課 我跟格蕾斯說我去送她\N{\rENG}Middle one's got a piano lesson. I told Grace I'd drive her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.76,0:19:50.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 格蕾斯的車壞了？    - 她討厭那輛車\N{\rENG}- Something wrong with Gracie's car?    - She hates that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.03,0:19:53.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,想把那輛舊車要回來 可是賣車的說他已經有買家了\N{\rENG}Wants the old one back, but the dealer said he's already got a buyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.50,0:19:55.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也許應該和賣車的談談\N{\rENG}Maybe I should talk to the dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:58.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我真是感激不盡\N{\rENG}I'd appreciate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.20,0:19:59.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.71,0:20:02.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 謝謝    - 回頭見\N{\rENG}- Thanks.    - See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.75,0:20:14.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,那傢伙按摩成癮 今天他不想按摩\N{\rENG}The man's a rubdown whore. Today he doesn't want one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.88,0:20:17.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在這裡到底幹不幹活？\N{\rENG}You ever do any work around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.48,0:20:20.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我是你的話 就不會操心我是不是幹活\N{\rENG}Not my job I'd worry about, if I was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.72,0:20:25.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,小姑娘看起來有進步啊\N{\rENG}Little girl seems to be coming along.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.85,0:20:31.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，看起來好象甚至有人在訓練她\N{\rENG}Yeah. It's almost like someone's been helping her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.79,0:20:36.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許她就是天生的 看起來她還有兩把刷子\N{\rENG}She might just be a natural. Looks like she's got something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.70,0:20:41.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,她還有我的梨球 她有的就這麼多\N{\rENG}She's got my speed bag, that's what she's got.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:43.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想知道她是怎麼弄到的\N{\rENG}I wonder how the hell she got that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:46.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也想知道\N{\rENG}I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.47,0:20:57.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想要拿回我的梨球\N{\rENG}I'm gonna need that speed bag back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.64,0:21:00.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這個？    - 沒錯，它是我的\N{\rENG}- This bag?    - Yes, that bag. That's my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.34,0:21:03.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你在這裡打它 別人會認為我在訓練你\N{\rENG}And if you're hitting it, people will think I'm training you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.36,0:21:05.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,老闆，這件事就這麼糟糕麼？\N{\rENG}Is that such a bad thing, boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.09,0:21:07.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,對，對，沒錯\N{\rENG}Yes. Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.22,0:21:10.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你每碰一次這個球 我就損失一些生意\N{\rENG}Every time you touch it, you're losing me business out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.59,0:21:14.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我得承認，我在這兒是丟人現眼    - 嗯\N{\rENG}- I gotta agree, I am embarrassing myself.    - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.47,0:21:17.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道，我不能把這個隨便借給別人\N{\rENG}Well, I can't just lend it to anybody, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.87,0:21:19.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我理解\N{\rENG}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:22.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:26.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看起來是個不錯的女孩\N{\rENG}Look, you seem like a nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.85,0:21:29.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我可以給你些建議麼？    - 感激不盡\N{\rENG}- Can I give you some advice?    - I'd appreciate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.98,0:21:32.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以在這裡或者其他地方...\N{\rENG}You'll find a trainer in this gym or somewhere else...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.68,0:21:34.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,...找到願意訓練女孩的訓練師\N{\rENG}...that's gonna wanna train a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.93,0:21:37.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,簡直就像是馬戲表演\N{\rENG}It's the latest freak show out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.29,0:21:39.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,問題是，他們只會浪費你的時間...\N{\rENG}The trouble is, they're gonna be wasting your time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.87,0:21:42.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,...因為你已經太老了\N{\rENG}...because you're too old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.63,0:21:44.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不覺得我那麼老了\N{\rENG}I don't feel that old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.37,0:21:48.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個嘛，我也不覺得我老 但是你看我還會和21歲的人打拳麼？\N{\rENG}Well, neither do I, but you don't see me fighting 21-year-olds, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.71,0:21:52.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,訓練一個拳擊手要四年\N{\rENG}Takes about four years to train a fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,你多大了？\N{\rENG}How old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.62,0:21:58.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 在下個生日之前31歲    - 噢，對呀，你看看\N{\rENG}- Thirty-one until my next birthday.    - Oh, well, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.05,0:22:00.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,31歲了\N{\rENG}Thirty-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:03.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會從31歲才開始練芭蕾舞，不是麼？\N{\rENG}You wouldn't start training to be a ballerina at 31, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.63,0:22:05.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經練了大概三年了\N{\rENG}Already been working it for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.93,0:22:09.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你連梨球都打不到？ 你到底怎麼訓練的？\N{\rENG}And you can't hit a speed bag? What kind of training is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.77,0:22:11.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,從來沒有人指導，老闆\N{\rENG}Never had any, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.57,0:22:15.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想說，可是能看出來\N{\rENG}Well, I hate to say it, but it shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.05,0:22:17.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是必須有人跟你說實話\N{\rENG}Somebody's gotta be honest with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.58,0:22:20.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,我討厭自己是那個說實話的人\N{\rENG}I hate to be the one to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.58,0:22:22.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.89,0:22:26.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,呃，對不起用了您的球，鄧先生\N{\rENG}Well, sorry for using your bag, Mr.Dunn.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.83,0:22:32.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你現在不會哭吧？    - 不會，先生\N{\rENG}- You're not gonna cry now, are you?    - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.33,0:22:34.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.61,0:22:38.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,給\N{\rENG}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.67,0:22:41.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這個該死的東西你留著吧    - 不，你需要它\N{\rENG}- Keep the goddamn thing.    - No, you need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.85,0:22:44.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,不，拿著吧\N{\rENG}No, take the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.55,0:22:47.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,反正我都二十年沒見過它了\N{\rENG}I haven't seen it in 20 years anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.15,0:22:51.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還有三個 好好享受它，好嗎？\N{\rENG}I've had three since then. Just enjoy it, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.72,0:22:54.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我只是在自己買之前暫時借用一下    - 嗯\N{\rENG}- I'll just borrow it till I buy my own.    - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.20,0:22:57.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,別丟了就行\N{\rENG}Just don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.58,0:23:07.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,對，我知道，霍根...\N{\rENG}Yeah, I know, Hogan...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.28,0:23:10.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,...你的拳手是冠軍 所以我們不能對半分...\N{\rENG}...your guy's the champ, so we don't split 50s...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.25,0:23:13.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,...但是如果我連四成--\N{\rENG}...but if I don't see 40 percent...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.79,0:23:18.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著，你同意六四開的時候再給我電話 要不然就別打來了\N{\rENG}Look, you call me back when it's 60-40 or don't call me back at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.34,0:23:29.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 嘿，威利    - 嘿，弗蘭基\N{\rENG}- Hey, Willie.    - Hey, Frankie.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.64,0:23:31.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,出什麼事情了麼？\N{\rENG}Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.41,0:23:35.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起我就這麼來找您 我知道你不喜歡別人來串門\N{\rENG}I'm sorry to come by your house like this. I know you don't like people dropping in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.94,0:23:39.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，你可不是外人，威利 什麼時候來我都歡迎，進來吧\N{\rENG}Oh, you're not people, Willie. You're welcome anytime. Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.51,0:23:42.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是來謝謝您幫格蕾斯把車拿回來\N{\rENG}I wanted to thank you for getting Gracie's car back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:44.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,哦，你不用謝我\N{\rENG}Oh, well, you don't have to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.02,0:23:48.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,為自己的車多花1000美元 也不算幫什麼忙\N{\rENG}Paying an extra thousand dollars for your own car ain't exactly a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.89,0:23:50.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,格蕾斯看見那輛車的時候都哭了\N{\rENG}Gracie cried when she saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.46,0:23:52.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,真的？\N{\rENG}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.53,0:23:55.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還想跟您談談業務上的事情\N{\rENG}I also needed to talk with you about business.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.86,0:23:59.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，對了，我剛和霍根通了電話 九月份的冠軍賽都談好了\N{\rENG}Oh, yeah, well, I just got off the phone with Hogan. We're all set for September.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.07,0:24:01.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,除了分成的問題\N{\rENG}Everything but the split.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.60,0:24:03.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我得離開你了，弗蘭基\N{\rENG}I gotta leave you, Frankie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:07.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.98,0:24:14.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,威利，再打兩場就到冠軍賽了\N{\rENG}Willie, the title's just two fights away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.32,0:24:18.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是這個問題，是-- 就好象你說的, 我只有一次機會\N{\rENG}It ain't that, it's... It's like you said, I got one shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.15,0:24:21.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我贏了，我就可以在我還能掙 的時候掙盡可能多的錢\N{\rENG}If I win, I gotta make as much as I can while I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.42,0:24:25.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要有人能幫我實現\N{\rENG}I need somebody in the action who can make things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.56,0:24:29.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,而且我得在比賽前換經理人\N{\rENG}And I gotta make the change before the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.56,0:24:32.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說必須讓他帶我去打冠軍賽 他才會簽下我\N{\rENG}Only way this guy say he'd take me is if he took me to the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.57,0:24:37.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我給你安排冠軍賽 然後他帶你去參加\N{\rENG}So I get you the title fight, and this guy takes you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.21,0:24:38.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說必須這樣\N{\rENG}Only way he'd do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.37,0:24:43.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,很抱歉，弗蘭基 我知道你等冠軍很久了\N{\rENG}I'm sorry, Frankie. I know how long you waiting on a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.34,0:24:44.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也希望能和你一起\N{\rENG}I wish it could've been with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.65,0:24:50.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,米奇 麥克是個生意人 他什麼也教不了你\N{\rENG}Mickey Mack's a businessman. He can't teach you nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.42,0:24:53.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,你已經教會了一切我需要知道的\N{\rENG}You already taught me everything I need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.26,0:25:05.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,有些話人們永遠都不願意聽\N{\rENG}There's some things people just don 't want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.08,0:25:20.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要挑戰“城市機動眼鏡蛇” 還有“刺客”湯馬斯 赫爾斯...\N{\rENG}And I challenge the Motor City Cobra, Thomas "Hit Man" Hearns...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.98,0:25:25.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,......爭奪次中量級世界冠軍！\N{\rENG}...to fight me for the welterweight championship of the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.45,0:25:28.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,丹吉爾，我這個拳套不是白戴的\N{\rENG}Danger, I'm wearing these mitts for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.46,0:25:32.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,只是練習一下我的步伐 斯科雷普先生\N{\rENG}Just working on my footwork, Mr.Scrap.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.09,0:25:37.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,丹吉爾，你打一拳 要不然就滾出去\N{\rENG}Danger, you throw a punch or get the hell out of this gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.44,0:25:44.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,丹吉爾，好好想想那一拳 我馬上就回來\N{\rENG}Danger, while you thinking about that punch, I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.24,0:25:50.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想我會狠狠打那一拳，斯科雷普先生\N{\rENG}I'm thinking how I'm gonna hit it hard for you, Mr.Scrap.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.32,0:26:01.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人忍心告訴丹吉爾 赫爾斯好多年前就已經退休了\N{\rENG}No one had the heart to tell Danger that Hearns retired years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.83,0:26:10.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,威利的事情我聽說了\N{\rENG}I heard about Willie.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.33,0:26:14.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常無情，太無情了\N{\rENG}That's cold. That's dead cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.40,0:26:17.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然，要不是你年紀都這麼大了 還不算太殘酷\N{\rENG}Of course, it wouldn't be so bad if you weren't so damn old.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.61,0:26:20.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯，至少我還能用兩只眼睛看\N{\rENG}Yeah, well, at least I can see through both eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.21,0:26:23.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過也沒給你帶來多少好處，不是嗎？\N{\rENG}Didn't do you a lot of good though, did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.58,0:26:26.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還有這個訓練館\N{\rENG}Well, I've got the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.58,0:26:29.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這個年紀也不用再訓練拳手了\N{\rENG}Don't need to be training fighters at my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.12,0:26:32.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,威利告訴你原因了？\N{\rENG}Willie tell you why?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.82,0:26:35.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,是米奇 米奇有他的關系\N{\rENG}It was Mickey. Mickey's got the connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.89,0:26:39.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,這不是因為關系 這是因為你對他沒有信心\N{\rENG}Oh, it ain't about connections. It's about you not believing in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.39,0:26:42.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我發掘了他 在他身上花了八年的心血\N{\rENG}Well, I found him, I stuck with him for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.26,0:26:43.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,這叫我對他沒信心？\N{\rENG}How's that for not believing in him?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.90,0:26:47.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩年前你就可以讓他去打冠軍賽了 他是知道的\N{\rENG}You could've got him a title fight two years ago. Hell, he knew that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.47,0:26:49.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,他能在你身邊呆這麼久 我都感到吃驚\N{\rENG}I'm amazed he stayed around this long.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.73,0:26:53.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個嘛，去參加比賽 和把腰帶贏回家完全是兩回事\N{\rENG}Well, getting there and taking home the belt are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.17,0:26:56.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我應該怎麼辦 讓他去參加贏不了的比賽？\N{\rENG}What was I supposed to do, just put him in over his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.24,0:26:57.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,不保護他？\N{\rENG}Not protect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.74,0:27:00.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,哦，你是在保護他不讓他拿冠軍？\N{\rENG}Oh, you were protecting him from the championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.30,0:27:03.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 對    - 唔，現在聽起來合情合理了\N{\rENG}- Yeah.    - Well, now it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.96,0:27:07.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你又怎麼樣呢，斯科雷普？ 你的經理當時做了什麼？\N{\rENG}Well, what about you, Scrap? What did your manager do?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.69,0:27:10.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,你曾經是多麼優秀的拳手 比威利要棒\N{\rENG}You were a hell of a fighter, better than Willie.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.53,0:27:13.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,他給了你一場冠軍賽 還是把你扔在那裡...\N{\rENG}He get you a title fight, or did he just bust you out...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.56,0:27:17.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,...讓對手用拳頭不停打你的頭 直到把眼睛打沒了？\N{\rENG}...banging your head against other people's fists until you lost your eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.53,0:27:19.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,至少我有個機會\N{\rENG}I had my shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.50,0:27:22.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我去揮舞過我的拳頭 沒有人能說我沒努力過\N{\rENG}I went out swinging, and no man can say I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.26,0:27:23.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，我記得\N{\rENG}Yeah, well, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.66,0:27:27.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是請不要因為 我不想讓我的拳手下半輩子...\N{\rENG}And excuse me if I didn't want my fighter spending the second half of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.59,0:27:31.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,- ...都在清掃別人吐在地上的口水而介意    - 嗯，是啊\N{\rENG}...cleaning up other people's spit.    - Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.56,0:27:35.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,對，你是聰明人 你還學希臘語呢\N{\rENG}Right, you're the smart one. You're the one learning Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.05,0:27:37.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,是高盧語\N{\rENG}It's Gaelic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.45,0:27:40.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你剛剛把自己參加 冠軍爭霸戰的機會保護沒了\N{\rENG}Well, you just protected yourself out of a championship fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.76,0:27:44.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,這句話用高盧語怎麼說？\N{\rENG}How do you say that in Gaelic?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.07,0:28:53.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉\N{\rENG}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.13,0:29:01.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.86,0:29:06.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,冠軍和大個子威利 瓊斯 之間的較量繼續進行...\N{\rENG}The action continues as the champ is battling Big Willie Jones...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.17,0:29:08.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,...他被冠軍用 連續的左右拳控制住了\N{\rENG}...and commanding him with rights and lefts.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.33,0:29:11.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,逼到了繩圈的邊上 他在用左拳攻擊....\N{\rENG}Up against the ropes, he's hitting him with the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.76,0:29:15.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,拳擊是一種不自然的運動\N{\rENG}Boxing is an unnatural act.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.33,0:29:18.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為拳擊中的每樣東西都是逆向的\N{\rENG}Because everything in it is backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.19,0:29:22.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想向左移動...\N{\rENG}You wanna move to the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.22,0:29:26.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,... 不是向左邁步 而是右腳趾用力\N{\rENG}...you don't step left, you push on the right toe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.73,0:29:30.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,向右移動的時候左腳趾用力\N{\rENG}To move right, you use your left toe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.43,0:29:34.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要迎著痛苦而上 而不是...\N{\rENG}Instead of running from the pain, like a sane person would do...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.52,0:29:36.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,...象有理智的人那樣躲避\N{\rENG}...you step into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.32,0:29:41.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,大個子威利反擊了，噢，天哪 他一記右手拳擊中了衛冕拳王\N{\rENG}But Big Willie comes back. Oh, my God, he hits the champ with a right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.66,0:29:44.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,衛冕拳王倒下了\N{\rENG}And the champ is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.25,0:29:46.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,女士們先生們 裁判正在數點\N{\rENG}Ladies and gentleman, the ref is in for the count.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.72,0:29:50.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,大個子威利 瓊斯 成為了新的世界冠軍\N{\rENG}And Big Willie Jones is the new champion of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.25,0:29:54.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,今晚發生的一切令人難以置信...\N{\rENG}It's unbelievable how this has taken place tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.05,0:29:58.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,...不過朋友們，新的冠軍產生了\N{\rENG}...but there you have it, folks, a new champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.91,0:30:02.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,拳擊中的每樣東西都是逆向的\N{\rENG}Everything in boxing is backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.27,0:30:19.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,要芝士漢堡嗎？\N{\rENG}Want a cheeseburger?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.14,0:30:21.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你給我買了個芝士漢堡？    - 嗯\N{\rENG}- You bought me a cheeseburger?    - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.11,0:30:23.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從沒見你給別人買過芝士漢堡\N{\rENG}I never see you buy anybody a cheeseburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.31,0:30:26.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我點了，可我吃不了，你願意吃麼？\N{\rENG}Well, I couldn't eat it, and I ordered it. You want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.51,0:30:30.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，我猜地球又開始轉了\N{\rENG}Well, I guess the planet can go back to spinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.91,0:30:35.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你看比賽了麼？    - 嗯，看了\N{\rENG}- You watch the fight?    - Yeah, I watched it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.07,0:30:37.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,威利打的不錯\N{\rENG}Willie did good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.27,0:30:40.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是你要說的？\N{\rENG}That's what you've got to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.07,0:30:43.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,威利贏了，不是嗎？ 他打的不錯\N{\rENG}Well, he won, didn't he? He did good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.67,0:30:48.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看出你正在改變自己 學著敞開心扉，很不錯\N{\rENG}I see you been working on yourself, learning to open up. That's good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.24,0:30:50.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看了？\N{\rENG}You watch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.23,0:30:53.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，我有HBO臺\N{\rENG}Yeah, I got HBO.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.30,0:30:55.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你怎麼可能看得起HBO？\N{\rENG}Now, how can you afford HBO?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.80,0:30:59.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從什麼時候起就叫你省錢了？\N{\rENG}How long have I been telling you to save your money?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.80,0:31:02.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,從我和“臺風”路易士 強森...\N{\rENG}Ever since I fought Louis "Typhoon" Johnson...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.50,0:31:05.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,...在密西西比州圖皮洛市的 俱樂部體育館比賽以後\N{\rENG}...at the Stadium Club in Tupelo, Mississippi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.56,0:31:07.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 真的？    - 是的\N{\rENG}- That true?    - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.72,0:31:11.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,經理人跑路了 讓我們自己搭車回家\N{\rENG}Manager ran off and left you and me to hitch home.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.56,0:31:13.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,你難道什麼都不記得了麼？\N{\rENG}Don't you remember nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.03,0:31:17.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我記得走到一半的時候 覺得自己要被私刑處死了\N{\rENG}Well, I remember walking halfway and thinking I was gonna be lynched.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.66,0:31:21.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我記得你把口袋空空的我 扔在那個加油站\N{\rENG}I remember you leaving me with my dick in my hand behind that gas station.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.74,0:31:25.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，我當時搭到一個便車 我一關上門那傢伙就開走了\N{\rENG}Yeah, well, I got a ride. The guy took off before I hardly closed the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.38,0:31:28.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,後來我不得不又往回走了兩英里\N{\rENG}I had to walk back two miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.06,0:31:32.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的良心占了上風 這就是原因\N{\rENG}Your conscience got the better of you, that's what.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.58,0:31:36.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,那他媽是什麼聲音？\N{\rENG}What the hell's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.96,0:31:39.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天是她的生日\N{\rENG}It's her birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.03,0:32:05.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的呼吸方法不對 這就是為什麼你大口喘氣\N{\rENG}You're not breathing right. That's why you're panting.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.41,0:32:07.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天是你生日，是嗎？\N{\rENG}So it's your birthday, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.72,0:32:10.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你多大了？\N{\rENG}How old does that make you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.42,0:32:13.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我32了，鄧先生\N{\rENG}I'm 32, Mr.Dunn.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.21,0:32:16.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在這裡慶祝 我又花了一年的時間洗盤子和當女招待\N{\rENG}I'm celebrating that I spent another year scraping dishes and waitressing...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.95,0:32:19.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從13歲就開始幹這些了\N{\rENG}...which is what I been doing since 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.12,0:32:24.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,根據您的理論 我37歲之前打不出一記象樣的拳...\N{\rENG}And according to you, I'll be 37 before I can even throw a decent punch...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.31,0:32:27.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,...打了這個梨球一個月 一點進展也沒有...\N{\rENG}...which after working this speed bag for a month and getting nowhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.22,0:32:29.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,...我現在認識到 上帝的現實也許就是這樣\N{\rENG}...I now realize may be God's simple truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.59,0:32:31.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,另外的現實是，我的哥哥在監獄裡\N{\rENG}Other truth is, my brother's in prison...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.90,0:32:35.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的妹妹假裝 自己的一個孩子還活著，詐騙福利金\N{\rENG}...my sister cheats on welfare by pretending one of her kids is still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.68,0:32:38.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我爸爸死了 我媽有312磅重\N{\rENG}...my daddy's dead, and my mama weighs 312 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.95,0:32:41.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我還有理智的話 我應該回家去\N{\rENG}If I was thinking straight, I'd go back home...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.90,0:32:46.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,找個二手的活動房屋 買個炸鍋，再來點夾心餅幹\N{\rENG}...find a used trailer, buy a deep fryer and some Oreos.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.78,0:32:50.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,問題是，這是唯一我喜歡做的事情\N{\rENG}The problem is, this is the only thing I ever felt good doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.52,0:32:54.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果對於拳擊來說我太老了 那我就一無所有\N{\rENG}If I'm too old for this, then I got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.40,0:32:56.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,這下你滿意了吧？\N{\rENG}That enough truth to suit you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.32,0:32:59.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是你的梨球？\N{\rENG}This your speed bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.79,0:33:03.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,把你的放在臺子後面了 真希望能說那是我用壞的\N{\rENG}Put yours behind the counter. Wish I could say I wore it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.14,0:33:08.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了，停一下，停一下\N{\rENG}Okay, just hold it. Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.49,0:33:11.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要教你幾件事情 然後給你找個訓練師\N{\rENG}I'll show you a few things, and then we'll get you a trainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.79,0:33:13.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,不用了，抱歉\N{\rENG}No, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.60,0:33:16.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你還打算討價還價？    - 是的，先生\N{\rENG}- You're in a position to negotiate?    - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:20.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，因為我知道如果你正確的訓練我 我會成為冠軍\N{\rENG}Because I know if you train me right, I'm gonna be a champ.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.86,0:33:23.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,我見過你看著我的樣子\N{\rENG}I seen you looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.70,0:33:26.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 是的，用憐憫的眼神    - 你不要這麼說\N{\rENG}- Yeah, out of pity.    - Don't you say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.81,0:33:30.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不要這麼說，如果不是事實的話\N{\rENG}Don't you say that if it ain't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.32,0:33:32.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要的是訓練師\N{\rENG}I want a trainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.33,0:33:36.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不要施捨 我也不要幫忙\N{\rENG}I don't want charity, and I don't want favors.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.95,0:33:43.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你不感興趣，那我還要繼續慶祝\N{\rENG}If you're not interested, then I got more celebrating to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.54,0:33:47.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,停，停，停\N{\rENG}Stop, stop, stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.81,0:33:52.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,該死，停下來 你到底在做什麼？\N{\rENG}Goddamn it, stop. What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.06,0:33:57.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.03,0:33:59.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我來教你--\N{\rENG}If I'm gonna take you on...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.63,0:34:03.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你一定不會後悔的    - 聽我說就行了\N{\rENG}- You won't never regret it.    - Look, just listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.30,0:34:06.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 如果我來教你--    - 我保證我會非常努力\N{\rENG}- If I take you on...    - I promise I'll work so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.31,0:34:08.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,天，這已經是個錯誤了\N{\rENG}God, this is a mistake already.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.68,0:34:12.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我聽著呢，老闆\N{\rENG}I'm listening, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.25,0:34:17.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我來教你，你一句話也不要說 你不能對我有疑問\N{\rENG}If I take you on, you don't say anything, you don't question me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.19,0:34:21.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要問我問題 除了“是，弗蘭基”以外什麼也不要說\N{\rENG}You don't ask why, you don't say anything except maybe, "Yes, Frankie."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.32,0:34:25.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有我會試著忘記 你是個女孩這個事實\N{\rENG}And I'm gonna try to forget the fact that you're a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.36,0:34:26.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就要求這麼多\N{\rENG}That's all I ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.76,0:34:29.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,另外如果你受傷了別對我哭\N{\rENG}And don't come crying to me if you get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.00,0:34:32.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好的    - 我們一言為定\N{\rENG}- Alrighty.    - We got a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.47,0:34:34.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒，還沒有\N{\rENG}No, not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.54,0:34:36.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我教你怎麼打拳\N{\rENG}I'm gonna teach you how to fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.67,0:34:39.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後給你找個經理人 我就放手不管了\N{\rENG}...then we'll get you a manager, and I'm off down the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.54,0:34:43.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我不想和你爭，不過--    - 別跟我爭，我們就這麼辦\N{\rENG}- I hate to argue with you, but...    - Don't argue, that's the way we're doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.31,0:34:47.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會教你一切你需要知道的 然後你自己去掙個一百萬美元\N{\rENG}I teach you all you need to know, and you go off and make a million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.25,0:34:50.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不管 被人打掉牙齒，我也不管\N{\rENG}I don't care. You get your teeth knocked out, I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.35,0:34:53.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想聽 這個東西就是這樣\N{\rENG}I don't wanna hear about it. That's just the way it's gonna be.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.72,0:34:55.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有這樣我才同意教你\N{\rENG}It's the only way I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.53,0:35:04.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.83,0:35:10.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,在訓練場裡我注意到一件事 你從來不移動你的腳\N{\rENG}Now, one of the things I've noticed around the gym is you never move your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.97,0:35:14.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,你總是呆呆的站在那裡 你必須要移動你的腳\N{\rENG}You stand there just flat-footed. You've gotta move your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.44,0:35:16.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我將教會你最有用的東西之一\N{\rENG}That's one of the best things I can teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.78,0:35:19.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼，你應該這麼做\N{\rENG}So here's what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.85,0:35:22.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,把自己-- 膝蓋彎曲一點\N{\rENG}You get yourself... Bend your knees a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.75,0:35:26.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,擺好運動姿態 就好像你打算要打什麼一樣\N{\rENG}Get in an athletic position. Look like you're gonna hit something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.66,0:35:31.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 怎麼做，老闆？    - 就--打--梨球就行了\N{\rENG}- Move them how, boss?    - Just... Go... Hit the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.43,0:35:35.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 停    - 我做錯什麼了？\N{\rENG}- Stop.    - What'd I do wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.40,0:35:37.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，你做錯了兩件事情\N{\rENG}Okay, you did two things wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.73,0:35:41.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,第一，你問了我一個問題 第二，你又問了一個問題\N{\rENG}One is you asked a question, and two is you asked another question.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.57,0:35:45.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我要你做的 不是要打得多麼狠\N{\rENG}Now, what I want you to do, it's not about hitting it hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.57,0:35:49.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,而是打得多麼好 所以看著我\N{\rENG}...it's how good you hit it. So watch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.68,0:35:51.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你願意的話可以和我一起數\N{\rENG}You can count with me if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.48,0:35:54.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是數數 數一的時候，我打一下球\N{\rENG}It's just count. On a one-count, I hit right through the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.48,0:35:56.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你能再示範一次麼？    - 數--\N{\rENG}- Can you show me that again?    - I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.65,0:35:58.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,數一就行了，拜託\N{\rENG}Just say "one," please.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.85,0:36:00.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 一    - 好\N{\rENG}- One.    - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.52,0:36:02.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 一，好    - 一\N{\rENG}- One. Okay.    - One.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.52,0:36:05.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,對，就說一 很好，很好\N{\rENG}Yeah, just say "one." That's good. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.83,0:36:10.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後我移動到我的右腳 你可以看到我的重心都轉移到右腳\N{\rENG}Then I move over to my right foot. You'll see my weight is shifting to my right foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.93,0:36:15.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後我用我的手背攻擊 就象用冰錐碎冰\N{\rENG}Then I hit it with my back of my hand, sort of like I'm chipping ice with an ice pick.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.04,0:36:21.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後我轉過來，轉移到我的左腳 然後用右手攻擊\N{\rENG}Then I come over, and I shift to my left foot, and I hit it with my right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.58,0:36:24.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,還是冰錐的動作\N{\rENG}And ice pick maneuver again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.31,0:36:27.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,再轉到右腳上 再攻擊右側\N{\rENG}And I come over on my right foot and hit it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.95,0:36:31.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,就看著我的腳步\N{\rENG}Don't watch anything but my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.13,0:36:46.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這麼做 不停練習\N{\rENG}Just do it like that. Just keep practicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.73,0:37:20.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,你示範他們怎麼站立 雙腳和肩膀平行\N{\rENG}You show them how to stand, keep their legs under their shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.98,0:37:32.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,訓練一名拳手 你必須在精神上把他們剝光\N{\rENG}To make a fighter, you gotta strip them down to bare wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.81,0:37:34.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,死了再休息\N{\rENG}Rest when you're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.48,0:37:36.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,過來\N{\rENG}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.65,0:37:43.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不能只是 叫他們忘記以前知道的事情...\N{\rENG}You can't just tell them to forget everything you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.49,0:37:46.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,... 你要叫他們從骨子裡忘記\N{\rENG}...you gotta make them forget it in their bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.56,0:37:52.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他們疲憊到只聽你的話\N{\rENG}Make them so tired they only listen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.07,0:37:57.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,只能聽見你的聲音 只做你叫他們做的事情，不做其他事\N{\rENG}Only hear your voice, only do what you say, and nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.30,0:37:58.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,腳步移動\N{\rENG}Move your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.71,0:38:00.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,腳步移動起來 移動起來讓我看\N{\rENG}Move your feet around. Let's see you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.46,0:38:18.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,教他們怎麼保持平衡 怎麼讓對手失去平衡\N{\rENG}Show them how to keep their balance and take it away from the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.13,0:38:22.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,別這麼低，看著我 右勾拳，然後向右\N{\rENG}Not so low. Look at me. Right hook and just turn right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.23,0:38:29.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,如何用右腳趾產生動力\N{\rENG}How to generate momentum off your right toe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.67,0:38:34.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,出刺拳時如何彎曲膝蓋\N{\rENG}And how to flex your knees when you fire a jab.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.75,0:38:45.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,如何在後退中攻擊 好讓對手在追擊你時有所顧忌\N{\rENG}How to fight backing up, so that the other guy doesn't wanna come after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.59,0:38:47.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後你要再全部教他們一遍\N{\rENG}Then you gotta show them all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.99,0:38:50.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,一遍又一遍...\N{\rENG}Over and over and over...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.36,0:38:53.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,...直到他們感覺一切與生俱來\N{\rENG}...till they think they were born that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.10,0:38:56.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,轉移\N{\rENG}Shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.53,0:38:58.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,轉移位置\N{\rENG}Shift away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.47,0:39:02.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了，今天就到這裡\N{\rENG}Okay. That's enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.80,0:39:06.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,不錯，好姑娘\N{\rENG}Good work. Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.54,0:39:10.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,老闆，你覺得我可以打比賽了麼？\N{\rENG}You think I ready for a fight, boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.73,0:39:36.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，你過來\N{\rENG}Hey. Hey, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.97,0:39:40.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你都喘不過氣了\N{\rENG}You're not breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.84,0:39:43.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,不想和你爭論\N{\rENG}Hate to disagree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.18,0:39:47.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一有壓力就喜歡屏住呼吸\N{\rENG}Every time you get under pressure, you're holding your breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.18,0:39:50.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 從現在開始別這麼做    - 好的\N{\rENG}- Now, stop doing that.    - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.78,0:39:53.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,除了這一點，我做得很好，是吧？\N{\rENG}But other than that, I'm doing pretty good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.62,0:39:57.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我是說，對于女孩來講    - 我不訓練女孩\N{\rENG}- I mean, for a girl.    - I don't train girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.96,0:40:02.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,老闆，你覺得我可以參加比賽了麼\N{\rENG}Think I might be ready for a fight, boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.30,0:40:05.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯，我們先找個經理人 然後我們再看看，好嗎？\N{\rENG}Well, we'll get a manager, and we'll find out, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.00,0:40:09.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是想找一個 可是你一直讓我抽不出時間來\N{\rENG}I'd like to, but you been keeping me too busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.88,0:40:18.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 有家人嗎，老闆？    - 什麼？\N{\rENG}- Got any family, boss?    - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.28,0:40:24.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看你把所有的時間都花在我的身上了 我不知道你有沒有家人\N{\rENG}You been spending all this time with me, I didn't know if you had any.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.59,0:40:26.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.56,0:40:30.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,呃，我是有個女兒，叫凱蒂\N{\rENG}Well, I've got a daughter, Katy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.69,0:40:32.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,她就是家人啊\N{\rENG}That's family.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.69,0:40:35.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是我們並不那麼親近\N{\rENG}We're not exactly close.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.23,0:40:37.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,她多重？\N{\rENG}How much she weigh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.97,0:40:40.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.43,0:40:43.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的家庭問題和體重成正比\N{\rENG}Trouble in my family comes by the pound.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.94,0:40:47.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,是嗎\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.87,0:40:49.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是很重\N{\rENG}Not very big.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.24,0:40:54.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,曾經很愛運動 不知道現在還有沒有堅持\N{\rENG}Used to be real athletic. Don't know if she kept it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.32,0:41:03.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼，你怎麼想？\N{\rENG}So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.99,0:41:05.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以參加比賽了麼？\N{\rENG}I ready for a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.63,0:41:13.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，賽利\N{\rENG}Hey, Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.07,0:41:16.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,過來一下，好嗎？\N{\rENG}Come here for a minute, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.01,0:41:21.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,弗蘭基，能不能到後面來跟我談談？\N{\rENG}Frankie, I need to see you in the back for a minute, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.44,0:41:24.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我能和你說句話麼？    - 賽利是個很優秀的經理人\N{\rENG}- Can I see you a minute?    - Sally here's a real good manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.96,0:41:29.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,他手下還有幾個拿過金手套的選手 想要女孩嗎，賽利？\N{\rENG}Has a couple of Golden Glove boys. Looking for a girl, Sally?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.10,0:41:31.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果有優秀人選的話\N{\rENG}I'm looking for a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.50,0:41:34.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,看，這不就有了\N{\rENG}Well, see, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.12,0:41:39.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興和你合作，小姐\N{\rENG}Nice working with you, girlie.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.89,0:41:45.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你有什麼事？    - 沒什麼，沒什麼\N{\rENG}- What'd you want?    - Nothing. It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.33,0:41:49.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒撒謊，我已經看過你訓練了 你的左拳很厲害\N{\rENG}I ain't lying, I've been watching you work. You got a hell of a left.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.87,0:41:51.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.18,0:41:57.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你要不要試試？ 看看是不是合適？\N{\rENG}So you wanna give this a try? See if it's a fit?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.02,0:42:02.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 噢，當然    - 好\N{\rENG}- Yeah, sure.    - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.36,0:42:05.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，因為我覺得你已經夠資格比賽了\N{\rENG}Because I think you're ready for a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.08,0:42:19.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,分開\N{\rENG}Break.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.89,0:42:23.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我到底做錯了什麼，賽利？ 每次我逼近都被她痛擊\N{\rENG}What am I doing wrong, Sally? Every time I get inside, she's on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.13,0:42:26.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,你做得很好 你就快把她拖垮了，繼續出拳\N{\rENG}You're doing great. You're wearing her down. Keep punching.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.00,0:42:29.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我不好，我要輸了    - 你就快把她拖垮了\N{\rENG}- I ain't doing great, I'm losing.    - You're wearing her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.98,0:42:33.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒事吧，親愛的？看得清嗎？\N{\rENG}You okay, honey? Can you see okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.32,0:42:36.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 加油    - 加油\N{\rENG}- Come on.    - Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.58,0:42:39.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,加油，加油！\N{\rENG}Come on, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.76,0:42:45.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯！\N{\rENG}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.70,0:42:54.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,今晚真不錯，不是嗎？\N{\rENG}Nice night, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.50,0:42:57.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,老天\N{\rENG}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.37,0:42:59.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,那姑娘是羅尼 華盛頓的拳手\N{\rENG}That's Lonnie Washington's girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.61,0:43:01.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常優秀的拳手\N{\rENG}Hell of a fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.37,0:43:03.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,11場全勝\N{\rENG}11-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.61,0:43:05.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,左拳，左拳舉起來\N{\rENG}Your left. Keep your left up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.35,0:43:12.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,羅尼旗下有很多優秀拳手\N{\rENG}Lonnie's got a lot of good fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.62,0:43:15.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,輕量級冠軍喬伊 阿達喬也在他旗下\N{\rENG}He's got Joey Adagio, lightweight champ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.92,0:43:17.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.79,0:43:19.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的左拳，該死\N{\rENG}Your left, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.53,0:43:25.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是我肯定不會選她做第一個對手 不過賽利是個好經理人\N{\rENG}Wouldn't have been my choice for her first fight, but Sally's a good manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.37,0:43:28.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 他一定認為她能打敗她    - 天哪\N{\rENG}- He must think she can take her.    - Jesus H.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.27,0:43:30.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,左拳，左拳舉起來\N{\rENG}Your left. Keep your left up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.34,0:43:34.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你認為這麼遠的地方她能聽見？\N{\rENG}You think she can hear you from back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.38,0:43:45.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然，就算麥琪輸了 對賽利也算不了什麼\N{\rENG}Of course, if Maggie loses, it wouldn't mean anything to Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.32,0:43:47.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許還對他有幫助\N{\rENG}Might even help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.49,0:43:49.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓羅尼的女選手再勝一場...\N{\rENG}Lonnie's girl gets another win...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.56,0:43:54.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,...羅尼也許會讓賽利的輕量級拳手 去挑戰喬伊 阿達喬的冠軍\N{\rENG}...Lonnie might let Sally's lightweight fight Joey Adagio for the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.39,0:43:56.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,賽利想要安排一場和阿達喬的比賽？\N{\rENG}Sally's trying to set a fight with Adagio?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.90,0:43:58.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，我知道什麼？\N{\rENG}Hey, what do I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.50,0:44:01.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是來欣賞比賽\N{\rENG}I just come because I enjoy the fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.40,0:44:03.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,上帝\N{\rENG}Mother of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.84,0:44:06.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了，分開\N{\rENG}Okay, break.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.51,0:44:08.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，過來，過來\N{\rENG}Hey. Come here, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.04,0:44:10.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，過來\N{\rENG}Hey. Get over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.61,0:44:13.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你老是放低左拳 別再放低左拳了\N{\rENG}You're dropping your left hand. Quit dropping your left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.61,0:44:16.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，弗蘭基 你能不能讓我跟我的拳手談談？\N{\rENG}Hey, Frankie, you mind if I talk to my fighter?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.52,0:44:19.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你幹得還真不賴啊 你也是這樣指導你的輕量級選手的？\N{\rENG}You're doing a hell of a job. Is this the way you advise your lightweight?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.42,0:44:22.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是鄧\N{\rENG}Dunn.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.19,0:44:24.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你在幹什麼？    - 我在說話，你在幹什麼？\N{\rENG}- What are you doing?    - I'm talking. What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.86,0:44:26.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這是你的拳手麼？    - 是我的拳手\N{\rENG}- Is this your fighter?    - It's my fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.09,0:44:30.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,真的不是那麼合適，賽利\N{\rENG}It ain't fitting real well, Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.50,0:44:33.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧，你來帶她 反正她也屁都不會打\N{\rENG}Fine, you take her. She can't fight worth a shit anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.80,0:44:38.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 誰告訴我到底怎麼回事    - 我遲到了，賽利剛才只是替我\N{\rENG}- Somebody tell me what's going on.    - I was late. Sally was just subbing for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.37,0:44:40.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說她是你的拳手？\N{\rENG}You telling me this is your fighter?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.01,0:44:45.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,對，是我的拳手\N{\rENG}Yeah, this is my fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.55,0:44:47.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼你有10秒的時間\N{\rENG}Then you got 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.51,0:44:50.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我把左手舉起來了 可當我出拳的時候，就總是會放下去\N{\rENG}I keep holding my left up, then I throw a punch and it keeps dropping.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.88,0:44:52.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 那就放下去好了    - 那就簡單多了\N{\rENG}- Well, let it drop.    - That'd be a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.12,0:44:54.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,她認為她摸透你了\N{\rENG}She thinks she knows you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.45,0:44:57.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你左手每次放下 她就從上面打過來\N{\rENG}Every time you drop it, she comes right over the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.66,0:45:00.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你就等著她，明白嗎？ 她腦子裡就這麼多東西\N{\rENG}So you just wait for her, see? That's all she's thinking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.06,0:45:04.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 她收回右拳準備出擊的時--你聽見了嗎?    - 我聽著呢，老闆\N{\rENG}- When she cocks that right hand... You hear?    - I hear you, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.23,0:45:07.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果她那麼做，你就向旁邊躲一步 然後給她一記再見勾拳\N{\rENG}When she does, step to the side and come with a good-night hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.40,0:45:08.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 能行嗎？    - 看我的吧\N{\rENG}- Got one?    - Got it right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.00,0:45:11.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好    - 開始吧，我等著呢\N{\rENG}- Okay.    - Fight, or I'm calling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.84,0:45:14.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 去教訓她吧    - 拳手的身體瞭解拳手自己所不瞭解的東西\N{\rENG}- Go give it to her.    - The body knows what fighters don 't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.01,0:45:16.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,如何保護自己\N{\rENG}How to protect itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.91,0:45:19.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,脖子只能轉動那麼多\N{\rENG}A neck can only twist so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.38,0:45:22.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,哪怕再多轉一毫米 身體就會說：\N{\rENG}Twist it just a hair more, and the body says:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.75,0:45:26.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,“嘿，還是讓我來吧 因為很明顯你不知道你自己在做什麼”\N{\rENG}"Hey, I'll take it from here because you obviously don't know what you're doing."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.09,0:45:28.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,到中立區去\N{\rENG}Neutral corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.39,0:45:32.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 看見她怎麼出拳了麼？    - 嗯\N{\rENG}- See the way she did that?    - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.43,0:45:35.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,舒格 雷就會這麼做 這女人好象他一樣\N{\rENG}Sugar Ray would do that. Girl's got sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.56,0:45:41.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,“躺下，休息 等你恢復知覺我們再談”\N{\rENG}"Lie down, now, rest, and we'll talk about this when you regain your senses."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.37,0:45:43.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個叫做擊倒心理\N{\rENG}It's called the knockout mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.77,0:45:47.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在放鬆一點 你幹得不錯\N{\rENG}Don't get all carried away, now. You did good.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.64,0:45:49.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝了，老闆\N{\rENG}Thanks, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.98,0:45:52.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你....你忘了規矩\N{\rENG}You... You forgot the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.48,0:45:54.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 告訴我規矩是什麼？    - 左手要抬起？\N{\rENG}- Now, what is the rule?    - Keep my left up?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.08,0:45:58.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,規矩是要隨時保護自己\N{\rENG}It's to protect yourself at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.62,0:46:00.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，規矩是什麼？\N{\rENG}Now, what is the rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.35,0:46:03.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 隨時保護我自己    - 很好，很好\N{\rENG}- Protect myself at all times.    - Good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.86,0:46:06.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,你放棄了我 那對我是什麼樣的保護？\N{\rENG}You gave me away. How was that protecting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.69,0:46:08.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,那不是保護\N{\rENG}It wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.00,0:46:11.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒關系了\N{\rENG}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.30,0:46:16.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我會練習我的左手的，老闆    - 把水喝了\N{\rENG}- I'll work on my left, boss.    - Drink your water.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.20,0:46:18.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,除了這一點，我怎麼樣？\N{\rENG}Other than that, how'd I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.34,0:46:22.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好，你做得很好\N{\rENG}Fine. You did fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.18,0:46:24.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還會再放棄我麼？\N{\rENG}You gonna leave me again?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.88,0:46:28.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,永遠不會\N{\rENG}Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.72,0:46:33.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,你工作的那個地方 有沒有手工制檸檬酥皮派？\N{\rENG}That place you work, do they have homemade lemon meringue pie there?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.62,0:46:36.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 當然有    - 不是罐裝餡料的那種垃圾\N{\rENG}- Sure.    - Not the kind with the canned-filling crap?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.42,0:46:40.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，是很大罐的那種 標簽上寫著“手工製作”\N{\rENG}Oh, big can, yay size. Says "homemade" on the label.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.60,0:46:45.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我想你這個週末休息一下    - 這才星期四\N{\rENG}- I want you to take the weekend off.    - It's only Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.87,0:46:50.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你打算要和我爭？    - 我知道最好不要有這個想法，老闆\N{\rENG}- You gonna argue with me?    - Know better than to do that, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.10,0:46:52.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯，很好\N{\rENG}Well, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.07,0:46:55.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,某種角度來看，拳手大都很頑固\N{\rENG}All fighters are pigheaded some way or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.21,0:46:59.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的某個部分總覺得 在某件事情上自己比別人知道的更多\N{\rENG}Some part of them always thinks they know better than you about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.78,0:47:04.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能不能花幾分鐘講講聖母懷胎？\N{\rENG}Can you spare a few minutes for the Immaculate Conception?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.65,0:47:09.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,實際上，就算他們錯了...\N{\rENG}Truth is, even if they're wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.69,0:47:12.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,...就算有那麼件事情 可以把他們都毀了...\N{\rENG}...even if that one thing is gonna be the ruin of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.86,0:47:17.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,...如果你能把他們徹底打敗 那他們就不算是拳手了\N{\rENG}...if you can beat that last bit out of them, then they ain 't fighters at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.86,0:47:21.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我記得我說過讓你週一再來    - 沒錯，老闆\N{\rENG}- Thought I said I'd see you Monday.    - You sure did, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.77,0:47:23.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是昨晚說的\N{\rENG}That was last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.20,0:47:26.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說不要和你爭論\N{\rENG}You said not to argue with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.42,0:47:40.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,該死的女人總是不按我的指揮做事\N{\rENG}Damn woman won't do a thing I tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.29,0:47:42.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,想聽我的建議麼？\N{\rENG}You want my advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.42,0:47:43.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.82,0:47:46.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的鞋子哪去了？\N{\rENG}Where are your shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.66,0:47:49.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我給我的腳透透風\N{\rENG}I'm airing out my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.43,0:47:53.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的襪子上凈是大洞\N{\rENG}You got big holes in your socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.33,0:47:56.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，沒有那麼大啦\N{\rENG}Oh, they're not that big.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.10,0:48:00.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不是給你錢去買新的了嗎？\N{\rENG}Didn't I give you money for some new ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.01,0:48:03.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我的睡襪\N{\rENG}These are my sleeping socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.08,0:48:07.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的腳晚上需要一些新鮮空氣\N{\rENG}My feet like a little air at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.31,0:48:10.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你為什麼要在白天穿它們？\N{\rENG}How come you're wearing them in the daytime, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:13.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為我白天穿的襪子上洞太多了\N{\rENG}Because my daytime socks got too many holes in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.02,0:48:21.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,那好，如果我多給你些錢 你能去買幾雙新的麼？\N{\rENG}Well, if I give you some more money, you buy some new socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.93,0:48:23.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,拜託？\N{\rENG}Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.93,0:48:29.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯，很有吸引力 不過我不能保證\N{\rENG}Well, I'd be tempted, but I couldn't say for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.94,0:48:31.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許會跑到跑道上去\N{\rENG}Might find its way to the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.39,0:48:51.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,比賽結束，比賽結束\N{\rENG}It's over. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.44,0:49:09.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥琪沒花多少時間就取得連勝\N{\rENG}Didn't take Maggie long to hit her stride.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.59,0:49:22.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我解決了呼吸的問題.\N{\rENG}I got the breathing thing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.19,0:49:25.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,不，你還是呼吸不正確 因為你第一回合就把對方打倒了\N{\rENG}No, you ain't breathing because you're knocking them out in the first round.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.93,0:49:29.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我還以為那就是重點    - 重點是讓自己變強\N{\rENG}- Thought that was the point.    - The point is to get good.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.10,0:49:32.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,把對方第一回合就擊倒 自己怎麼可能進步\N{\rENG}Can't get good if you keep knocking them out first round.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.87,0:49:35.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我怎麼給你再找到對手？\N{\rENG}How am I gonna get you fights?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.84,0:49:39.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人願意自己的拳手被羞辱\N{\rENG}Nobody wants to see their fighter embarrassed, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.34,0:49:41.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼我還要 打這種四回合比賽，老闆？\N{\rENG}Why am I still doing four-rounders, boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.51,0:49:44.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為你的肺還打不了六回合\N{\rENG}Because you haven't got the lungs for six rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.91,0:49:48.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一直這麼在第一回合 就把她們擊倒就行了\N{\rENG}I do if I keep knocking them out in the first round.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.05,0:49:55.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,弗蘭基讓她又打了場四回合比賽...\N{\rENG}Frankie made her fight one more four-rounder...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.46,0:49:57.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,...只是讓她明白誰說了算數\N{\rENG}...just to let her know who was boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.69,0:50:04.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,三，四，五...\N{\rENG}Three, four, five...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.86,0:50:06.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,...六，七....\N{\rENG}...six, seven...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.70,0:50:08.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉，老闆\N{\rENG}Sorry, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.94,0:50:10.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥琪對此毫不懷疑\N{\rENG}Maggie left no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.40,0:50:23.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了，加油\N{\rENG}All right, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.77,0:50:28.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是第一場六回合賽並沒那麼輕松\N{\rENG}Her first six-rounder didn't go quite as smooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.50,0:50:44.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,起來！\N{\rENG}Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.86,0:50:46.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,到你的角落去\N{\rENG}To your corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.33,0:50:49.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 三，四，五...    - 起來\N{\rENG}- Three, four, five...    - Get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.66,0:50:52.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,- ...六，七...    - 起來\N{\rENG}...six, seven...    - Get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.06,0:50:55.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,- ...八，九，十，比賽結束    - 你能做到\N{\rENG}...eight, nine, ten. It's over.    - You can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.39,0:51:00.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥琪到了第一回合結尾才將對方擊倒\N{\rENG}Maggie didn't knock her out till the end of the first round.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.99,0:51:05.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,在那以後，沒有經理願意 讓自己的拳手和麥琪交手\N{\rENG}After that, no manager wanted to put his fighter in with Maggie.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.19,0:51:12.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,弗蘭基不得不自己討腰包 來給她安排比賽...\N{\rENG}Frankie had to go into his pocket to get her decent fights...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.42,0:51:17.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,...靠給對方經理人賄賂 來增加對方參賽的興趣\N{\rENG}...sweetening the purse by paying managers on the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.45,0:51:31.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,這並沒能持續太久\N{\rENG}That only worked for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.08,0:51:34.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後弗蘭基做了他不願意做的事\N{\rENG}Then Frankie did something he hated doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.39,0:51:36.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,他冒了次險\N{\rENG}He took a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.18,0:51:40.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,開始\N{\rENG}Box.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.28,0:51:46.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,他把她晉升了一個級別\N{\rENG}He moved her up in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.95,0:51:50.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,這差點成為一個錯誤\N{\rENG}That could've been a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.67,0:52:04.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,注意右邊！\N{\rENG}Watch the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.44,0:52:09.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,注意，注意\N{\rENG}Watch it. Watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.54,0:52:20.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,分開，分開，後退，時間到\N{\rENG}Break, break. Step back. Break. Time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.99,0:52:31.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,該死，該死，該死\N{\rENG}Damn, damn, damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.93,0:52:34.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我們兩秒鐘，好嗎？\N{\rENG}Give us two seconds, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.56,0:52:36.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好    - 兩秒鐘就好\N{\rENG}- Okay.    - Just two seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.10,0:52:39.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你的鼻樑骨斷了    - 噢，該死\N{\rENG}- Your nose is broke.    - Oh, damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.50,0:52:41.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 弄好它    - 我沒辦法，我沒辦法\N{\rENG}- Fix it.    - I can't, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.44,0:52:44.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你可以的    - 我不行，我準備棄權了\N{\rENG}- You can fix it.    - I can't. I've gotta call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.14,0:52:46.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我見你做過，弄好它\N{\rENG}I've seen what you can do. Fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.41,0:52:49.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我能把它按回去 但是我不能給你止血\N{\rENG}I can snap it back into place, but I can't stop the bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.41,0:52:51.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,醫務裁判會中止比賽的\N{\rENG}The ring doctor's gonna call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.11,0:52:55.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,求你，弗蘭基，你要是能幫我止血 我就能打倒她\N{\rENG}Please, Frankie, if you can stop the blood, I can beat her.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.81,0:52:58.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,咬住這個\N{\rENG}Bite down on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.91,0:53:17.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 吸氣    - 什麼？\N{\rENG}- Inhale.    - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.54,0:53:19.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 吸氣    - 什麼\N{\rENG}- Inhale.    - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.41,0:53:21.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,吸氣\N{\rENG}Breathe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.36,0:53:35.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 可以？    - 嗯，沒問題\N{\rENG}- Okay, huh?    - Yeah, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.33,0:53:38.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，這個變成噴泉之前你有20秒鐘...\N{\rENG}All right, you got 20 seconds before this turns into a geyser...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.60,0:53:40.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,...血會噴到整個前排座位上的\N{\rENG}...and it's gonna spray all over the front row.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.91,0:53:43.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,你只有20秒\N{\rENG}Twenty seconds, that's all you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.27,0:53:45.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,去吧\N{\rENG}Now get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.76,0:54:00.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,回到你的角落去\N{\rENG}Go to your corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.76,0:54:03.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,三，四，五...\N{\rENG}Three, four, five...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.70,0:54:07.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 加油，呼吸，呼吸    - ...六，七，八...\N{\rENG}- Come on, breathe. Breathe. ...six, seven, eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.57,0:54:10.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,...九，十\N{\rENG}...nine, ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.07,0:54:15.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.15,0:54:22.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好！    - 太棒了！\N{\rENG}- All right!    - Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.72,0:54:25.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.36,0:54:31.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在讀什麼\N{\rENG}What you reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.03,0:54:33.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說什麼？\N{\rENG}What's she saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.86,0:54:36.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,想知道你在讀什麼\N{\rENG}Wants to know what you're reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.40,0:54:39.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,是葉芝的作品（愛爾蘭著名詩人） 仰著點頭\N{\rENG}It's Yeats. Keep your head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.14,0:54:42.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,你為什麼不跟她說說葉芝呢？\N{\rENG}Why don't you talk a little Yeats to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.27,0:54:45.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴她那是怎樣一件樂事\N{\rENG}Show her what a treat that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.48,0:54:47.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,他媽的什麼時候才能輪到她？\N{\rENG}When the hell they gonna get to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.61,0:54:50.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很好，弗蘭基\N{\rENG}I'm okay, Frankie.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.62,0:54:53.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你今天學到了什麼？    - 隨時保護自己\N{\rENG}- What'd you learn tonight?    - Always protect myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.75,0:54:57.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 規矩是什麼？    - 隨時保護自己\N{\rENG}- What's the rule?    - Always protect myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.03,0:54:59.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 麥琪 菲斯傑拉德?    - 在這裡\N{\rENG}- Margaret Fitzgerald?    - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.43,0:55:06.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就在這兒等你\N{\rENG}I'll be right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.35,0:55:19.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你怎麼樣？    - 我？\N{\rENG}- How you doing?    - Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.99,0:55:22.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 對，你    - 我又沒有受傷\N{\rENG}- Yeah, you.    - I'm not the one who's hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.83,0:55:29.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,鼻子斷了並不是那麼受傷\N{\rENG}Broken nose don't hurt that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.39,0:55:32.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼你要告訴我這個？\N{\rENG}Why are you telling me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.86,0:55:35.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有原因\N{\rENG}No reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.36,0:55:39.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,可有些傷太深了 或是離骨頭太近\N{\rENG}But some wounds are too deep or too close to the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.91,0:55:44.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管你如何努力，都不能止血\N{\rENG}And no matter how hard you work at it, you just can't stop the bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.58,0:55:48.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你給你女兒寫信了麼？    - 每週都寫\N{\rENG}- Did you write your daughter?    - Every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.48,0:55:53.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我真不明白你為什麼要來教堂\N{\rENG}I've no idea why you come to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.69,0:56:29.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,在連續十二場比賽擊倒對手勝出後 弗蘭基得到幾個非常不錯的邀請\N{\rENG}After her 12th straight knockout, Frankie got a couple of real good offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.97,0:56:33.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,第一個邀請是和 “蘭熊”比麗 奧斯特曼...\N{\rENG}The first was to fight Billie "The Blue Bear" Osterman...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.74,0:56:36.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,...爭奪WBA次中量級頭銜\N{\rENG}...for the WBA welterweight title.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.05,0:56:40.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,“蘭熊”比麗\N{\rENG}Billie "The Blue Bear."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.01,0:56:43.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,比麗原來是東柏林的妓女\N{\rENG}Billie was a former prostitute out of East Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.31,0:56:48.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,她是這個級別裡 手法最骯臟的拳手，臭名遠揚\N{\rENG}Had a reputation for being the dirtiest fighter in the ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.94,0:57:07.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,她看起來一點也不在乎...\N{\rENG}Didn't seem to matter to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.54,0:57:10.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,...這樣的動作可能會致人於死地\N{\rENG}...that something like that could kill a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.08,0:57:13.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,觀眾喜歡她\N{\rENG}And the crowds loved her.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.22,0:57:19.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,他沒告訴她就把這場比賽拒絕了.\N{\rENG}He turned it down without even telling her.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.35,0:57:21.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,下一個邀請是去挑戰英國冠軍\N{\rENG}The next was to fight the British champ...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.78,0:57:25.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 一個剛被比麗擊敗的牙買加女孩    - 喂？\N{\rENG}- ...a Jamaican girl Billie just beat.    - Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.88,0:57:28.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,不感興趣\N{\rENG}Not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.71,0:57:33.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,他也沒接受那個邀請\N{\rENG}He turned that down too.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.43,0:57:37.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,可是很大一筆錢哪，老闆\N{\rENG}That's a lot of money, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.89,0:57:41.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，你掙錢了 為什麼還在這裡工作？\N{\rENG}Yeah, you're making money. What are you still working here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.52,0:57:43.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是冠軍賽，對吧？\N{\rENG}It's a title match, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.39,0:57:46.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是英國人麼？ 那個冠軍你拿不走的\N{\rENG}Are you British? It's a title you can't take away.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.54,0:57:50.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,她沒什麼好輸的 你也沒什麼好贏的\N{\rENG}She's got nothing to lose, you got nothing to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.67,0:57:53.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,很可能仍然是一場不錯的比賽呢\N{\rENG}Might still be a good fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.40,0:57:57.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，我剛把你升上次中量級\N{\rENG}Yeah, I just... I just brought you up to welterweight.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.10,0:58:00.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,能和跟你水準相當的選手打就不錯了 還想他媽去挑戰那些冠軍？\N{\rENG}Too good to fight these contenders, you'd rather fight some bullshit champ?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.72,0:58:04.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒發現有和我水準相當的選手啊\N{\rENG}Didn't notice I was fighting any contenders.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.52,0:58:08.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你想的話 隨時可以換經理\N{\rENG}Well, you can get yourself another manager any time you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.78,0:58:11.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,實際上，如果你有能力 把自己的臉保護得好一點的話...\N{\rENG}In fact, if you'd learn to protect your face a little better...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.84,0:58:15.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,...我才不會拒絕這筆錢呢\N{\rENG}...I wouldn't have to turn down this money.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.70,0:58:22.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的臉暴露出那麼多 可還沒被擊倒過，真是個奇跡\N{\rENG}My face is out there so much it's a miracle I haven't been knocked out yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.99,0:58:53.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,你今晚不要繼續訓練了\N{\rENG}No, you can't work here anymore tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.89,0:58:56.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我定了位子\N{\rENG}I made us a reservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.03,0:59:02.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,你去洗個澡吧\N{\rENG}You might wanna shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.85,0:59:24.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的\N{\rENG}Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.19,0:59:26.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的\N{\rENG}Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.56,0:59:28.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是什麼？\N{\rENG}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.43,0:59:31.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想要的東西 這不是什麼秘密\N{\rENG}Well, it ain't no big secret what you're wishing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.26,0:59:33.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,把蠟燭吹了\N{\rENG}Go on and blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.64,0:59:40.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.47,0:59:46.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,33歲不算大的\N{\rENG}Thirty-three ain't so old.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.71,0:59:50.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,我39歲的時候還在參賽\N{\rENG}I was still fighting at 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.85,0:59:54.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我打了23年\N{\rENG}Fought for 23 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.12,0:59:59.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,最近怎麼樣，斯科雷普\N{\rENG}How's it going, Scrap?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.96,1:00:01.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,不錯，米奇\N{\rENG}Doing good, Mickey.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.69,1:00:04.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,不錯\N{\rENG}Doing good.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.90,1:00:08.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你要什麼？    - 咖啡\N{\rENG}- What'll you have?    - Coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.94,1:00:16.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們兩個不講話？\N{\rENG}You two not speaking?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.64,1:00:18.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,不太認識他\N{\rENG}Don't hardly know him.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.81,1:00:28.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在37歲生日之後遇到了弗蘭基\N{\rENG}I met Frankie right after my 37th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.05,1:00:31.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,那時他幹的工作是給拳手包紮傷口\N{\rENG}He was picking up cut work.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.59,1:00:36.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我認為不可能的時候 他總能給我包紮好\N{\rENG}He used to patch me up when I thought it was impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.63,1:00:39.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,有他在賽場邊真不錯\N{\rENG}Good man to have in your corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.56,1:00:42.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rENG}Yes, he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.07,1:00:47.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我最後一次比賽，在聖伯蒂諾 他也陪了我全場\N{\rENG}He stayed with me through my last fight in San Berdu.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.07,1:00:51.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的經理喝醉了，不知所蹤\N{\rENG}My manager was off getting drunk somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.08,1:00:55.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有我和弗蘭基\N{\rENG}...and it was just Frankie and me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.41,1:01:00.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我被打得暈頭轉向\N{\rENG}I was taking a hellacious beating.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.69,1:01:05.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,每個人最多能參加多少比賽 都有個數字\N{\rENG}Everybody's got a particular number of fights in him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.72,1:01:08.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人告訴你那個數字是多少\N{\rENG}Nobody tells you what that number is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.59,1:01:12.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的是109場\N{\rENG}Mine was 109.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.86,1:01:15.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是不願承認\N{\rENG}I just didn't want to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.90,1:01:19.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,第四回合\N{\rENG}Fourth round, this...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.94,1:01:21.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡被打開了口子\N{\rENG}...cut opens up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.84,1:01:24.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,鮮血擁進我的眼睛裡\N{\rENG}Blood starts pouring into my eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.54,1:01:30.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們本應該終止那場比賽的 但是，媽的，我是個在聖伯蒂諾的黑人\N{\rENG}They should've stopped the fight, but, hell, I was a black man in San Berdu.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.71,1:01:32.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,我到那裡就是去流血的\N{\rENG}Blood was what I was there for.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.75,1:01:37.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,一回合接著一回合 我不斷地讓弗蘭基給我包紮\N{\rENG}Round after round, I kept getting Frankie to patch me up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.89,1:01:39.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,他想扔毛巾認輸...\N{\rENG}He's talking about throwing in the towel...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.06,1:01:43.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,...但他不是我的經理人 什麼也不能扔\N{\rENG}...but he ain't my manager, he can't throw in nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.43,1:01:46.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,一回合接著一回合...\N{\rENG}Round after round...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.86,1:01:49.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,...他一直跟我爭吵\N{\rENG}...he's arguing with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.57,1:01:54.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我幾乎是在笑他，因為，媽的 好象是打在他身上似的\N{\rENG}And I'm almost laughing because, hell, it's getting more to him than to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.57,1:01:58.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我打了15回合\N{\rENG}I go 15 rounds...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.24,1:02:00.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,裁判判我輸了\N{\rENG}...Iose by decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.14,1:02:03.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,第二天早上，我的眼睛沒了\N{\rENG}Next morning, I lose the eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.02,1:02:09.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,23年來，他從來沒說起過這件事\N{\rENG}In 23 years, he's never said a thing about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.49,1:02:14.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒這個必要 每次他看我，我都能從他的臉上讀出來\N{\rENG}Doesn't have to. I can see it in his face every time he looks at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.39,1:02:17.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,某種程度上\N{\rENG}Somehow...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.16,1:02:20.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,弗蘭基認為自己應該終止那場比賽\N{\rENG}...Frankie thinks he should've stopped that fight...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.70,1:02:24.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,可以挽救我的眼睛\N{\rENG}...should've saved my eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.27,1:02:30.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,他一生都希望能收回那第109場比賽\N{\rENG}Spends his life wishing he could take back that 109th fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.21,1:02:34.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我卻想參加第110場\N{\rENG}I wanted to go to 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.74,1:02:36.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,重點是\N{\rENG}Thing is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.38,1:02:39.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你想取得冠軍\N{\rENG}...if you wanna get to the title...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.52,1:02:43.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許他並不是最好人選\N{\rENG}...maybe he's not the one to take you there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.43,1:02:50.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你告訴了麥克先生我們今晚會來這裡？\N{\rENG}You tell Mr.Mack we'd be here tonight?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.73,1:02:55.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續吃你的蛋糕吧\N{\rENG}You go on, eat your cupcake.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.13,1:02:58.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,不用了，我來吧\N{\rENG}No, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.41,1:03:05.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是規矩\N{\rENG}It's the rule.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.98,1:03:08.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,隨時保護自己\N{\rENG}Always protect yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.95,1:03:11.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,人們從不采納自己的意見\N{\rENG}People never take their own advice.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.95,1:03:16.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果她要離開弗蘭基 最好當時就做\N{\rENG}If she was gonna leave Frankie, better she did it to him then.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.32,1:03:23.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,米奇 麥克先生？\N{\rENG}Mr.Mickey Mack?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.46,1:03:25.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是麥琪 菲斯傑拉德\N{\rENG}I'm Maggie Fitzgerald.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.10,1:03:31.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我聽說你是非常好的經理人 給大個子威利做的很不錯\N{\rENG}I hear you're a real good manager, doing good things for Big Willie.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.27,1:03:35.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我想你該知道 我是不會離開鄧先生的\N{\rENG}But I thought you should know I ain't never leaving Mr.Dunn...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.27,1:03:39.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以你不需要再找藉口好遇見我了\N{\rENG}...so you don't need to make any more excuses to bump into me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.31,1:03:43.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,不好意思打攪你吃飯了\N{\rENG}Sorry for interrupting your dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.45,1:03:51.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥琪總是喜歡剛一交手 就把對手擊倒\N{\rENG}Maggie always did like taking them out in the first round.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.79,1:04:28.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,寄出的信總是原樣退回:\N{\rENG}The letters always came back marked the same way:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.83,1:04:31.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,上面寫著“退還發件人”\N{\rENG}"Return to sender."
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.56,1:05:03.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我給你準備點咖啡\N{\rENG}I'll make you some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.06,1:05:06.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你打算拿你的錢幹些什麼？\N{\rENG}What are you doing with your money?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.33,1:05:09.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 存起來    - 好孩子\N{\rENG}- Saving it.    - Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.27,1:05:14.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道，如果存夠了就可以買座小房\N{\rENG}You know, you save enough of it, you ought to get yourself a little house.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.84,1:05:16.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,現金，不用貸款\N{\rENG}Cash, no mortgage.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.34,1:05:18.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,那還要存一段時間\N{\rENG}Gonna be a while before I can do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.01,1:05:25.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊，可能還有一段時間...\N{\rENG}Yeah, well, it might be a stretch...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.42,1:05:28.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,...但你得給自己弄個窩\N{\rENG}...but you gotta get yourself a place of your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.22,1:05:31.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,把錢浪費在無關緊要的東西上 你能得到什麼？\N{\rENG}Go around wasting it on things that don't matter and what do you got?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.86,1:05:33.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,明白麼？\N{\rENG}You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.59,1:05:37.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,很快，如果你等得太久 你什麼也得不到\N{\rENG}Pretty soon, you wait long enough, you got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.56,1:05:39.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧，只要我存夠錢\N{\rENG}Okay, soon as I get the money.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.73,1:05:43.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這一生中犯了很多錯誤 我只是不想你走一樣的路\N{\rENG}I made a lot of mistakes in my life. I'm just trying to keep you from doing the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.27,1:05:45.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道了，老闆\N{\rENG}I know, boss.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.20,1:05:49.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我不會長命百歲的    - 這是什麼？\N{\rENG}- I'm not gonna live forever.    - What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.84,1:05:52.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,一盒關於你那個英國對手的錄像帶\N{\rENG}It's a tape on that girl in England you're gonna fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.78,1:05:56.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你想去爭奪冠軍 我們得做-- 嘿！\N{\rENG}If you're gonna go for the title, we got some moves to... Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.18,1:05:58.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，快他媽下來 知道我有多大歲數麼？\N{\rENG}Hey, get the hell down. You know how old I am?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.02,1:06:01.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 謝謝老闆，非常感謝    - 嗯\N{\rENG}- Thank you, boss. Thank you so much.    - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.82,1:06:06.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,不用謝，親愛的 給，把--我把這個放到機器裡去\N{\rENG}You're welcome, darling. Here, just... Here, let me put this in the machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.42,1:06:08.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼機器？\N{\rENG}What machine?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.06,1:06:10.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,你沒有電視，是麼？\N{\rENG}Don't have a TV, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.79,1:06:12.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.23,1:06:14.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,耶！\N{\rENG}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.50,1:06:18.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了，好的\N{\rENG}All right. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.27,1:06:26.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 還有十分鐘，親愛的    - 謝謝\N{\rENG}- Ten minutes, love.    - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.08,1:06:28.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,那傢伙說他愛我\N{\rENG}Man says he loves me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.68,1:06:30.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不可能是第一個這麼說的男人\N{\rENG}He's probably not the first one to say that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.95,1:06:33.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,除了我爸以外的第一個\N{\rENG}First since my daddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.82,1:06:35.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要是贏了，你說他會向我求婚麼？\N{\rENG}I win, you think he'll propose?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.85,1:06:37.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,你贏了，我就向你求婚\N{\rENG}You win, I'll propose.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.79,1:06:43.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,看，我給你帶了件禮物\N{\rENG}Look, I got you a gift here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.93,1:06:50.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想這是其他人的吧\N{\rENG}I think they gave you somebody else's.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.93,1:06:52.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,不，不，就是這個\N{\rENG}No, no, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.94,1:06:55.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”是什麼意思？\N{\rENG}What's it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.57,1:06:59.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,不知道，是高盧語\N{\rENG}I don't know. Just something in Gaelic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.34,1:07:04.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 真漂亮    - 嗯，我也這麼認為\N{\rENG}- It's beautiful.    - Yeah, I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.21,1:07:06.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 是啊    - 真絲的\N{\rENG}- Yeah.    - Real silk thread.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.65,1:07:13.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,來自美國的挑戰者...\N{\rENG}From the United States of America, the challenger...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.16,1:07:17.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,...麥琪 菲斯傑拉德\N{\rENG}...Maggie Fitzgerald.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.26,1:07:21.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒” 你看到她袍子上的字了嗎？\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle. Did you see what was on her robe?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.53,1:07:23.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,- “莫 庫什勒”，“莫 庫什勒”    - “莫 庫什勒”\N{\rENG}- Mo cuishle. Mo cuishle.    - Mo cuishle.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.00,1:07:29.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,她本不是本晚的賣點\N{\rENG}She wasn 't the main attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.04,1:07:33.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,她的比賽是一場中量級拳王賽的墊場賽\N{\rENG}She was on the undercard of a middleweight title fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.08,1:07:36.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,但如果你問問在場的人...\N{\rENG}But ask someone who was there...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.25,1:07:39.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,...他們都不記得 當晚參加比賽的其他選手了\N{\rENG}...they couldn 't tell you who else fought that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.39,1:07:47.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,開始\N{\rENG}Box.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.61,1:08:09.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 加油！    -“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}- Come on!    - Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.81,1:08:13.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.18,1:08:16.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.12,1:08:19.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.09,1:08:24.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.87,1:08:34.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,她很強\N{\rENG}She's tough.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.31,1:08:38.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我無法靠近 我無法靠近打到她\N{\rENG}I can't get inside. I can't get close enough to hit her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.91,1:08:41.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你知道為什麼嗎？    - 為什麼？\N{\rENG}- You know why that is?    - Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.81,1:08:43.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為她是個比你更好的拳手\N{\rENG}She's a better fighter than you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.91,1:08:48.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,她更年輕，更強壯 更有經驗\N{\rENG}She's younger, she's stronger, and she's more experienced. Now...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.18,1:08:50.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在你打算怎麼辦？\N{\rENG}...what are you gonna do about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.43,1:09:00.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,去吧\N{\rENG}Get in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.93,1:09:02.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,開始\N{\rENG}Box.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.15,1:09:20.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,三，四，五，六..\N{\rENG}Three, four, five, six...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.08,1:09:26.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,...七，八，九，十\N{\rENG}...seven, eight, nine, ten.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.96,1:09:30.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.67,1:09:41.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,- “莫 庫什勒”！    - “莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}- Mo cuishle!    - Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.18,1:09:50.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道我可以問其他人，對嗎？\N{\rENG}I could ask someone, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.91,1:09:52.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,好啊\N{\rENG}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.42,1:09:54.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道以後告訴我\N{\rENG}You find out, you let me know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.69,1:10:04.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管那個名字是什麼意思 人們記住了\N{\rENG}Whatever it meant, the name stuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.63,1:10:09.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥琪打遍愛丁堡，巴黎，布魯塞爾 和阿姆斯特丹\N{\rENG}Maggie fought in Edinburgh and Paris, Brussels and Amsterdam.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.37,1:10:12.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,觀眾總是高呼“莫 庫什勒”\N{\rENG}It was always mo cuishle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.44,1:10:14.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,看起來到處是愛爾蘭人...\N{\rENG}Seems there are Irish people everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.94,1:10:17.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,...或者是想成為愛爾蘭人的人\N{\rENG}...or people who wanna be.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.67,1:10:20.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,當他們回到美國的時候...\N{\rENG}By the time they came back to the States...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.01,1:10:24.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,...麥琪已經達到了一個新的水準\N{\rENG}...Maggie was in a whole new league.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.23,1:10:45.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！“莫 庫什勒”！\N{\rENG}Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.55,1:10:58.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,後來他們受到另一場冠軍賽的邀請\N{\rENG}After that they got another offer to fight for the title.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.08,1:11:02.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼分成？\N{\rENG}What's the split?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.52,1:11:05.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 六四開    - 好\N{\rENG}- Sixty-forty.    - Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.12,1:11:10.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，我們六，你們四 因為麥琪是吸引觀眾的籌碼\N{\rENG}We'll take 60 and you take 40, being as that Maggie's the draw.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.59,1:11:11.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個小女孩\N{\rENG}That little girl?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.40,1:11:15.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,你真的認為我說的不對？ 你認為觀眾會說...\N{\rENG}You think I'm wrong, really? You think people are saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.90,1:11:19.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,...他們想看一個破爛德國人 痛揍無名氏小姐？\N{\rENG}...that they wanna see some scabby Kraut beat up on little Miss What's-Her-Name?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.87,1:11:22.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要能找到那樣的人，我們就拿四\N{\rENG}You find someone who says that, and we'll take the 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.48,1:11:32.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,給你\N{\rENG}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.08,1:11:38.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們現在是六四開 不過最後會是五五開\N{\rENG}They're at 60-40, but they'll come up to 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.66,1:11:41.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,那女孩現在怎麼樣了？\N{\rENG}How's that girl doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.56,1:11:44.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,她腦震蕩了，耳鼓膜破裂\N{\rENG}Well, she's got a concussion and a broken eardrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.86,1:11:46.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,她沒事吧\N{\rENG}She be all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.06,1:11:50.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 她要是有事呢？    - 也許我應該給她送點什麼\N{\rENG}- And if she isn't?    - Maybe I should send her something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.03,1:11:55.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你願意的話，把你的獎金寄給她好了 我想她會接受\N{\rENG}Well, you could send her your check if you'd like. I'm sure she'd take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.21,1:12:01.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,老闆？\N{\rENG}Boss?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.14,1:12:04.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們說起過的那座房子？\N{\rENG}That little house we talked about?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.65,1:12:05.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我買下了\N{\rENG}I bought it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.55,1:12:08.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,聰明的姑娘\N{\rENG}Well, smart girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.55,1:12:13.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我媽買的 離她現在住的地方不到一英里\N{\rENG}For my mama. It's only about a mile from where she lives now.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.52,1:12:15.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,如你所言，沒有貸款\N{\rENG}No mortgage, just like you said.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.89,1:12:19.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是個好女兒\N{\rENG}You're a good daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.63,1:12:22.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,她還不知道\N{\rENG}She don't know about it yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.90,1:12:26.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望我們可以多待一天 開車到那裡去\N{\rENG}I was hoping maybe we could stay an extra day, drive over there?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.60,1:12:28.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道她想見你\N{\rENG}I know she wants to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.21,1:12:33.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧，可以\N{\rENG}Yeah, we could do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.79,1:12:53.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,哦，天哪，媽媽快出來\N{\rENG}Oh, my God. Mama, come on out here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.13,1:12:56.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥琪回來了\N{\rENG}Mary M's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.38,1:13:17.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這是約翰遜家的舊屋    - 不再是了\N{\rENG}- This is the Johnsons' old house.    - Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.16,1:13:24.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,它是你的了，媽媽 還有瑪代爾和孩子們\N{\rENG}It's all yours, Mama. For you and Mardell and the kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.16,1:13:28.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 麥琪，這房子是你給我買的？    - 對，是你的了，全部付清了\N{\rENG}- Mary M, you bought this for me?    - Yeah, all yours, free and clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.13,1:13:30.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,親愛的\N{\rENG}Darling...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.07,1:13:33.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒冰箱，也沒爐灶\N{\rENG}There's no fridge. No stove neither.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.50,1:13:35.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,在你們搬進來前，會準備好的\N{\rENG}They'll be here before you move in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.04,1:13:39.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你花了多少錢？    - 你不用管\N{\rENG}- How much money did this cost you?    - Never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.61,1:13:42.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你不該這麼做    - 您需要一個體面的住處\N{\rENG}- You shouldn't have done this.    - You need a decent place.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.48,1:13:45.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不該這麼做 你該先問問我的\N{\rENG}You shouldn't have done it. You should've asked me first.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.15,1:13:50.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果政府發現了 他們會停掉我的社會福利的\N{\rENG}Government's gonna find out about this, they're gonna stop my welfare.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.55,1:13:54.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 媽媽，他們不會的    - 他們會的，你很好，有自己的工作\N{\rENG}- Mama, no, they ain't.    - They are. You're fine, you're working...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.56,1:13:56.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,但沒有福利我活不下去\N{\rENG}...but I can't live without my welfare.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.59,1:13:58.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,媽媽我會給你寄錢的\N{\rENG}Mama, I'll send you money.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.53,1:14:01.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,醫療怎麼辦？ 公費醫療會把我從名單上劃掉\N{\rENG}What about my medicine? Medicaid gonna cut me off.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.00,1:14:05.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我拿什麼錢買藥啊？    - 我會給你寄更多的錢\N{\rENG}- How am I supposed to get my medicine?    - I'll send you more money.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.97,1:14:08.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望你沒有預期JD要住進來\N{\rENG}I hope you don't expect J.D. To move in with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.40,1:14:09.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道他快出獄了\N{\rENG}He's getting out, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.44,1:14:12.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼不把錢直接給我？\N{\rENG}Why didn't you just give me the money?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.88,1:14:16.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼必須給我買房子？\N{\rENG}Why'd you have to buy me a house?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.65,1:14:22.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是必須，媽媽，但房子是你的了\N{\rENG}I didn't have to, Mama, but it's yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.42,1:14:24.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果想要錢，把它賣掉好了\N{\rENG}You want the money, sell it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.13,1:14:32.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不--\N{\rENG}I don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.30,1:14:41.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道你不想傷害我們...\N{\rENG}I know you didn't mean nothing hurtful...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.37,1:14:43.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,...只是有時候你沒把事情想清楚\N{\rENG}...but sometimes you just don't think things through.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.94,1:14:47.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這倒是真的，媽媽    - 我會試著不把房子賣掉\N{\rENG}- That's true, Mama.    - I'll try and keep the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.98,1:14:50.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是擔心養房子的那些費用\N{\rENG}I'm just worried about all those expenses.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.48,1:14:52.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會給你寄更多錢的\N{\rENG}I'll send you some more money.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.56,1:15:03.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個人把你打成這樣的？\N{\rENG}That man hitting you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.33,1:15:07.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是比賽留下的\N{\rENG}It's from the fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.86,1:15:09.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是一名拳擊手，媽媽\N{\rENG}I'm a fighter, Mama.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.30,1:15:12.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,找個老公吧，麥琪\N{\rENG}Find a man, Mary M.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.44,1:15:14.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,過正常的生活\N{\rENG}Live proper.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.27,1:15:17.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,人們知道你的職業後就會嘲笑你\N{\rENG}People hear about what you're doing and they laugh.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.44,1:15:20.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴你我很難過，但是他們嘲笑你\N{\rENG}Hurts me to tell you, but they laugh at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.19,1:16:13.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.09,1:16:46.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,你養過狗麼？\N{\rENG}You ever own a dog?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.59,1:16:48.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rENG}Nope.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.29,1:16:52.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我差點養了一隻巴斯頓的中型狗\N{\rENG}Closest I ever came was a middleweight from Barstow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.93,1:16:59.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我爸養過一隻德國牧羊犬，埃克斯\N{\rENG}My daddy had a German shepherd, Axel.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.47,1:17:01.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,埃克斯的後腿不太好\N{\rENG}Axel's hindquarters were so bad...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.34,1:17:04.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,它得用自己的前腿拖著自己 從一個房間走到另一個房間\N{\rENG}...he had to drag himself room to room by his front legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.11,1:17:08.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,看他跑過廚房的地板\N{\rENG}Me and Mardell would bust up laughing...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.25,1:17:12.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我和瑪代爾都會忍不住大笑\N{\rENG}...watching him scoot across the kitchen floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.58,1:17:16.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸，他當時病的很重 自己都站不起來\N{\rENG}Daddy, he was so sick by then, he couldn't hardly stand himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.72,1:17:21.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,但一天早上他起床以後 把埃克斯抱到他的拖車上\N{\rENG}But one morning he got up, carried Axel to his rig...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.46,1:17:25.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們倆跑進樹林裡 又唱又叫\N{\rENG}...and the two of them went off into the woods, singing and howling.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.63,1:17:30.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,直到那天晚上他獨自回來時\N{\rENG}But it wasn't till he got home that night alone that I saw...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.27,1:17:32.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我才發現卡車裡的鏟子\N{\rENG}...the shovel in the back of the truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.88,1:17:40.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,好想再看看他們倆在一起的樣子\N{\rENG}Sure miss watching the two of them together.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.62,1:17:52.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我現在除了你誰都沒有了，弗蘭基\N{\rENG}I got nobody but you, Frankie.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.39,1:17:57.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,對，你還有我\N{\rENG}Well, you've got me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.73,1:18:03.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,至少在你找到一個好經理人以前是這樣\N{\rENG}At least, that is, until we find you a good manager.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.88,1:18:15.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，我們能在這停一下麼？\N{\rENG}Hey, can we stop just up here?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.15,1:18:17.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.42,1:18:21.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡有附近最好的檸檬派\N{\rENG}This place has the best lemon pie around.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.52,1:18:24.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有那種惡心的罐裝餡\N{\rENG}None of that canned-filling crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.04,1:18:41.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我可以上天堂了\N{\rENG}Now I can die and go to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.58,1:18:48.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我以前和爸爸常來這\N{\rENG}I used to come here with Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.72,1:18:52.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道象這樣的地方會不會出售\N{\rENG}Wonder if a place like this is for sale.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.42,1:18:54.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還有點積蓄\N{\rENG}I got a little bit of savings.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.70,1:19:01.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,（艾記小吃店）
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.99,1:19:04.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，好，謝謝\N{\rENG}That's fine, fine, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.23,1:19:11.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，丹吉爾到底在看什麼？\N{\rENG}Hey, what the hell's Danger looking at?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.14,1:19:14.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,好像是另外一瓶水\N{\rENG}Looks like another bottle of water.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.57,1:19:16.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,想和我們一起到拉斯維加斯去麼？\N{\rENG}Wanna come to Vegas with us?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.28,1:19:22.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,看你們在老虎機那兒受罪？ 我的心臟受不了那種刺激\N{\rENG}Watch you suffer over the nickel slots? My heart can't take that kind of pounding.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.21,1:19:25.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,呃，她有場冠軍賽，對手是“蘭熊”\N{\rENG}Well, she's got a title shot. The Blue Bear.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.98,1:19:28.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,百萬美金對半分\N{\rENG}Million dollars, split right down the center.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.19,1:19:29.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,啊，不錯啊，弗蘭基，很不錯\N{\rENG}That's good, Frankie. That's real good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.16,1:19:31.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想找個好助手一起去\N{\rENG}Well, I could use a good second.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.92,1:19:33.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是找不到 所以我來問問你\N{\rENG}Can't find one, I thought I'd ask you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.86,1:19:35.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,哦，我他媽為什麼會同意呢？\N{\rENG}Now, why the hell would I wanna do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.50,1:19:40.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為你是一個 從來沒得過冠軍的半瞎的老傻瓜\N{\rENG}Well, because you're a half-blind old fool who never got there himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.73,1:19:44.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想你可能想去體驗一下 站在冠軍賽的繩圈裡的感覺\N{\rENG}I thought you might like to feel what it's like to be in a ring on a title match.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.64,1:19:46.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,不好意思，我替你遺憾了\N{\rENG}Excuse me for feeling sorry for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.81,1:19:50.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不去，你還是在拉斯維加斯找吧\N{\rENG}No, you pick up somebody there in Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.81,1:19:53.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,找個年輕點的\N{\rENG}Somebody with young hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.68,1:19:56.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會哭吧？ 我已經帶上一個女孩了\N{\rENG}You're not gonna cry now, are you? I've already got one girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.55,1:20:00.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我離開這地方一天...\N{\rENG}I leave this place for one day...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.59,1:20:03.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,...知道回來時這裡會變成什麼樣麼？\N{\rENG}...got any idea what it would look like when I come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.59,1:20:05.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,和現在這樣差不多吧\N{\rENG}Kind of like it looks right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.59,1:20:07.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，去死吧\N{\rENG}Oh, go to hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.83,1:20:11.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴麥琪沒有拳王腰帶不要回來\N{\rENG}You tell Maggie don't come back here without a belt.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.33,1:20:13.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道了\N{\rENG}Will do.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.97,1:20:19.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，斯科雷普先生\N{\rENG}Hey, Mr.Scrap.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.11,1:20:23.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有個問題 可是我覺得問出來好傻\N{\rENG}I got a question, but I feel real stupid asking it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.58,1:20:25.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這裡沒有問題是愚蠢的，丹吉爾\N{\rENG}No such thing as a stupid question there, Danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.98,1:20:27.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.05,1:20:34.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你怎麼把冰塊從這麼小的口裡放進去的？\N{\rENG}How'd you get all the ice in here through this little tiny hole?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.29,1:20:36.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一直在想\N{\rENG}I've been thinking on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.52,1:20:38.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,但想不出來\N{\rENG}Can't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.46,1:20:40.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我來做給你看吧，丹吉爾\N{\rENG}Why don't I show you, Danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.26,1:20:43.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你可以，你可以做給我看？    - 我想可以，我想可以\N{\rENG}- You could do that? You could show me?    - I think so. I think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.80,1:20:48.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有，斯科雷普先生 我有點覺得我準備好參加比賽了\N{\rENG}Also, Mr.Scrap, I was kind of thinking I might be ready for a fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.64,1:20:55.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我拿了票，你準備好了麼？\N{\rENG}Well, I got the tickets. You ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.31,1:20:58.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們坐飛機去？    - 你寧願開車？\N{\rENG}- We're flying?    - Would you rather drive?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.58,1:21:01.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是問我嗎？\N{\rENG}You're asking me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.91,1:21:04.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是想坐飛機還是開車過去？\N{\rENG}Would you rather fly, or would you rather drive?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.35,1:21:07.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我終於有權決定某些事了麼？\N{\rENG}So I finally get to decide something?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.82,1:21:09.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我說的就是這個意思\N{\rENG}That's what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.76,1:21:10.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.16,1:21:12.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,好，飛過去，開車回來\N{\rENG}Fly there, drive back.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.36,1:21:16.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我聽過的最愚蠢的事 我們怎麼會那麼做？\N{\rENG}That's the stupidest thing I've ever heard. How the hell we gonna do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.23,1:21:18.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說過讓我決定的\N{\rENG}You said it was up to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.01,1:21:31.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,丹吉爾，給他們點顏色\N{\rENG}Give them hell there, Danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.44,1:21:34.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，老傢伙，馬桶的水溢出來了\N{\rENG}Hey, old school, the toilet's overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.82,1:21:41.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿，冒失鬼，過來一下\N{\rENG}Hey, Flippy, come here for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.62,1:21:45.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的天啊\N{\rENG}Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.66,1:21:48.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,老天爺\N{\rENG}Jesus, Mary and Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.69,1:21:50.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢，上帝！\N{\rENG}Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.23,1:21:56.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,蠢豬\N{\rENG}Dumb-ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.94,1:21:59.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,來呀，丹吉爾 來呀，丹吉爾\N{\rENG}Come on, Danger. Come on, Danger.
